Class AbstractGelfTransport

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.graylog2.gelfclient.transport.AbstractGelfTransport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GelfTransport
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GelfTcpTransport, GelfUdpTransport

    public abstract class AbstractGelfTransport
extends Object
implements GelfTransport
    An abstract GelfTransport implementation serving as parent for the concrete implementations.

    This class is thread-safe.

      • send

        public void send(GelfMessage message)
          throws InterruptedException
        Sends the given message to the remote host. This blocks until there is sufficient capacity to process the message. It is not guaranteed that the message has been sent once the method call returns because a queue might be used to dispatch the message.

        This implementation is backed by a BlockingQueue. When this method returns the message has been added to the BlockingQueue but has not been sent to the remote host yet.

        Specified by:
        send in interface GelfTransport
        Parameters:
        message - message to send to the remote host
        Throws:
        InterruptedException

      • trySend

        public boolean trySend(GelfMessage message)
        Tries to send the given message to the remote host. It does not block if there is not enough capacity to process the message. It is not guaranteed that the message has been sent once the method call returns because a queue might be used to dispatch the message.

        This implementation is backed by a BlockingQueue. When this method returns the message has been added to the BlockingQueue but has not been sent to the remote host yet.

        Specified by:
        trySend in interface GelfTransport
        Parameters:
        message - message to send to the remote host
        Returns:
        true if the message could be dispatched, false otherwise
